Meningitis, meningococcal - Mozambique 980716225031
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 1998 10:07:17 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on meningitis in Mozambique were extracted
from the GIDEON software program:
An outbreak of meningococcal meningitis during July to September 1995
involved 1,416 cases (118 fatal) in Napula and Niassa Provinces. An
outbreak in Cabo Delgado Province, Northern region involved 2,132 cases
(121 fatal) in 1996. Only 101 cases of
'meningitis' (18 fatal) were reported nationwide in 1997.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
